items.title: Awesome Ruby
items.content_text:
### Code Formatting

*   [RuboCop (‚≠ê13k)](https://github.com/rubocop-hq/rubocop) - A static code analyzer, based on the community Ruby style guide.
    *   [Rubocop Rails (‚≠ê843)](https://github.com/rubocop-hq/rubocop-rails) - A RuboCop extension focused on enforcing Rails best practices and coding conventions.
    *   [Rubocop Rspec (‚≠ê831)](https://github.com/rubocop-hq/rubocop-rspec) - Code style checking for RSpec files
    *   [Rubocop Performance (‚≠ê711)](https://github.com/rubocop-hq/rubocop-performance) - A RuboCop extension focused on code performance checks.

### Core Extensions

*   Attributes
    *   [ActiveAttr (‚≠ê1.2k)](https://github.com/cgriego/active_attr) - What ActiveModel left out.
    *   [Virtus (‚≠ê3.8k)](https://github.com/solnic/virtus) - Attributes on Steroids for Plain Old Ruby Objects.
    *   [AttrExtras (‚≠ê563)](https://github.com/barsoom/attr_extras) - Takes some boilerplate out of Ruby with methods like attr\_initialize.

### Date and Time Processing

*   [working\_hours (‚≠ê532)](https://github.com/intrepidd/working_hours) - A modern ruby gem allowing to do time calculation with working hours.

### Form Builder

*   [Rapidfire (‚≠ê327)](https://github.com/code-mancers/rapidfire) - Making dynamic surveys should be easy!

### Scientific

*   [Red Data Tools](https://github.com/red-data-tools) - Data processing tools for Ruby.

### Third-party APIs

*   [Buffer (‚≠ê56)](https://github.com/bufferapp/buffer-ruby) - Buffer API Ruby Library
items.content_html:

items.title: Awesome Network Analysis
items.content_text:
### Software / R

*   [backbone](https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=backbone) - Provides methods for binarizing a weighted network retaining only significant edges.
    *   [Introduction to the backbone package](https://arxiv.org/abs/1912.12779)
*   [networkdata (‚≠ê142)](https://github.com/schochastics/networkdata) - Includes 979 network datasets containing 2135 networks.
*   [snahelper](https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=snahelper) - RStudio addin which provides a GUI to visualize and analyse networks
    *   [Introduction to snahelper (Part 1)](http://blog.schochastics.net/post/an-rstudio-addin-for-network-analysis-and-visualization/)
    *   [Introduction to snahelper (Part 2)](http://blog.schochastics.net/post/new-rstudio-addins-for-network-analysis/)
